          "response_container": {
            "pointer": "left"
          },
          "stimulus": "<h4><span style=\"color:#daa520;\"><strong>TASK 4: HOW TO INCLUDE RESEARCH IN YOUR WORK</strong></span></h4>\n\n<h5>Watch the following video from USU, which gives a brief introduction to referencing and citation, then drag and drop the correct words to complete the text below</h5>\n<iframe allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/tbhKAIXDRes\" title=\"YouTube video player\" width=\"560\"></iframe>",
          "template": "<p>When you use research in your writing it is essential to show where the information comes from. We do this by&nbsp;&nbsp;{{response}}, the author and date of publication in our text and by including full details of the source in a <span id=\"cke_bm_19417S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;{{response}}<span id=\"cke_bm_19417E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;at the end of our assignment. Different institutions use different <span id=\"cke_bm_19417S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;{{response}}<span id=\"cke_bm_19417E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;systems. At Coventry Univerisity London, we use <span id=\"cke_bm_19417S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;{{response}}<span id=\"cke_bm_19417E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>, and full information on how to do this can be found on the Library Website. If you do not&nbsp; use {{response}}, this means you are not giving credit to the author and you are 'stealing' their ideas or research. This is a serious offence at University, and is known as&nbsp;<span id=\"cke_bm_19417S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;{{response}}<span id=\"cke_bm_19417E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>. It can result in lower grades or even failing a course. Make sure you&nbsp;&nbsp;<span id=\"cke_bm_19417S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;{{response}}<span id=\"cke_bm_19417E\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;correctly to avoid&nbsp; problems when you submit your work!</p>\n\n<p>In the next section we will look at two different methods of putting research into our writing</p>\n\n<p>{{response}}&nbsp;- including the exact words from the source</p>\n\n<p>{{response}}&nbsp;- including information or ideas from the source using our own words</p>\n",
