          "stimulus": "<h5><span style=\"color:#4b0082;\"><span style=\"font-size:1.5em;\"><img class=\"lrn-image-left\" height=\"34\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/755/475c43ad-c73a-4836-b960-3ab3fa6d021d.png\" width=\"50\" /><strong>TASK 5: Quoting, Paraphrasing &amp; Summarising</strong></span></span></h5>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.5em;\"></span><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\"><strong>In task 4 we mentioned the&nbsp;different ways to CITE source material in your work. In the following exercise, read the description and label the examples appropriately</strong></span></p>\n",
          "template": "<h5><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\"><u><strong>How do we use them in our work?</strong></u></span></h5>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\"><br>\n<strong>Quoting&nbsp;</strong>involves copying short sentences or passages from the original text word-for-word places copied wording within “quotation marks”. You also need to give the page number.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">Below is an example of how to include a quotation in your writing using the APA7 reference style. (This is the style used at Coventry University and you will use it for all your assessments)</span><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\"></span></p>\n\n<p>EXAMPLE:&nbsp;{{response}}</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\"><br>\n<strong>Paraphrasing&nbsp;</strong>involves putting a section of a text into your own words changes the words and phrasing of the original text, but keeps the original meaning of the text.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\">Below is an example of how to include a paraphrase in your writing using the APA7 reference style.</span><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\"></span></p>\n\n<p><span id=\"cke_bm_81524S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>EXAMPLE:&nbsp;{{response}}</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:1.3em;\"><br>\n<strong>Summarising&nbsp;</strong>involves stating the main ideas and findings of a text into your own words presents a general overview, so is usually much shorter than the original text. Below is an example of how to include a summary in your writing using the APA7 reference style.</span></p>\n\n<p><span id=\"cke_bm_81524S\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</span>EXAMPLE:&nbsp;{{response}}</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n",
